From a871d4264d293b57de9628c5c4a90e12f77e051f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Capivara CI <ci@capivara.dev>
Date: Wed, 24 Jun 2026 02:38:11 -0300
Subject: [PATCH 7/9] host/gl: implement the missing angle_shader_translator C
 ABI

CMakeLists.txt's USE_ANGLE_SHADER_PARSER comment says "the caller of the
cmake script is responsible to create the angle_shader_translator
target" -- but no caller (Meson build, AOSP platform tree mirrored here,
or any fork history checked) ever did. angle_shader_parser.cpp dlopen()s
"libshadertranslator.{dylib,so,dll}" and resolves a flat C ABI (ST_*
types, STInitialize/STCompileAndResolve/etc.) that doesn't exist
anywhere in this tree, in vanilla ANGLE, or in this repo's history.

Add ShaderTranslator.{h,cpp}: a thin wrapper translating that ST_* ABI
to ANGLE's real public API (sh::Initialize/ConstructCompiler/Compile/
GetUniforms/... in GLSLANG/ShaderLang.h), built as a standalone
cc_shared_library (//host/gl/glestranslator/gles_v2:shadertranslator)
linked against @angle//:translator. Wire USE_ANGLE_SHADER_PARSER into
meson.build (gated on decoders=gles, never set before -- it only existed
as an unwired CMake option), and add a Meson custom_target that invokes
Bazel to build the shim and drops the resulting dylib next to
libgfxstream_backend so it's on the existing DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH/
LD_LIBRARY_PATH entry.

ST_ShaderVariable/ST_InterfaceBlock field set was derived from actual
consumers (program_data.cpp's struct/uniform-block validation logic),
not guessed -- compiling against real callers caught a missing
isRowMajorLayout field during this work.

Validated: full decoders=vulkan,gles,composer meson+ninja build succeeds
end to end; dlopen+dlsym+call of STInitialize() from a standalone test
returns success. NOT YET validated against a real Android boot
exercising the GLES decoder -- the actual shader compile/link path is
untested beyond this.
